propertyAttribute.label: has member
propertyAttribute.comment: A UserAccount that is a member of this Usergroup.

propertyAttribute.label: links to
propertyAttribute.comment: Links extracted from hyperlinks within a SIOC concept, e.g. Post or Site.

propertyAttribute.label: next version
propertyAttribute.comment: Links to the next revision of this Item or Post.

propertyAttribute.label: usergroup of
propertyAttribute.comment: A Space that the Usergroup has access to.

propertyAttribute.label: has part
propertyAttribute.comment: An resource that is a part of this subject.

propertyAttribute.label: scope of
propertyAttribute.comment: A Role that has a scope of this resource.

propertyAttribute.label: administrator of
propertyAttribute.comment: A Site that the UserAccount is an administrator of.

propertyAttribute.label: has owner
propertyAttribute.comment: A UserAccount that this resource is owned by.

propertyAttribute.label: later version
propertyAttribute.comment: Links to a later (newer) revision of this Item or Post.

propertyAttribute.label: reference
propertyAttribute.comment: Links either created explicitly or extracted implicitly on the HTML level from the Post.

propertyAttribute.label: link
propertyAttribute.comment: A URI of a document which contains this SIOC object.

propertyAttribute.label: earlier version
propertyAttribute.comment: Links to a previous (older) revision of this Item or Post.

propertyAttribute.label: feed
propertyAttribute.comment: A feed (e.g. RSS, Atom, etc.) pertaining to this resource (e.g. for a Forum, Site, UserAccount, etc.).

propertyAttribute.label: space of
propertyAttribute.comment: A resource which belongs to this data Space.

propertyAttribute.label: addressed to
propertyAttribute.comment: Refers to who (e.g. a UserAccount, e-mail address, etc.) a particular Item is addressed to.

propertyAttribute.label: about
propertyAttribute.comment: Specifies that this Item is about a particular resource, e.g. a Post describing a book, hotel, etc.

propertyAttribute.label: has modifier
propertyAttribute.comment: A UserAccount that modified this Item.

propertyAttribute.label: has container
propertyAttribute.comment: The Container to which this Item belongs.

propertyAttribute.label: topic
propertyAttribute.comment: A topic of interest, linking to the appropriate URI, e.g. in the Open Directory Project or of a SKOS category.

propertyAttribute.label: modifier of
propertyAttribute.comment: An Item that this UserAccount has modified.

propertyAttribute.label: has host
propertyAttribute.comment: The Site that hosts this Forum.

propertyAttribute.label: has usergroup
propertyAttribute.comment: Points to a Usergroup that has certain access to this Space.

propertyAttribute.label: follows
propertyAttribute.comment: Indicates that one UserAccount follows another UserAccount (e.g. for microblog posts or other content item updates).

propertyAttribute.label: embeds knowledge
propertyAttribute.comment: This links Items to embedded statements, facts and structured content.

propertyAttribute.label: latest version
propertyAttribute.comment: Links to the latest revision of this Item or Post.

propertyAttribute.label: subscriber of
propertyAttribute.comment: A Container that a UserAccount is subscribed to.

propertyAttribute.label: container of
propertyAttribute.comment: An Item that this Container contains.

propertyAttribute.label: has creator
propertyAttribute.comment: This is the UserAccount that made this resource.

propertyAttribute.label: has moderator
propertyAttribute.comment: A UserAccount that is a moderator of this Forum.

propertyAttribute.label: avatar
propertyAttribute.comment: An image or depiction used to represent this UserAccount.

propertyAttribute.label: attachment
propertyAttribute.comment: The URI of a file attached to an Item.

propertyAttribute.label: creator of
propertyAttribute.comment: A resource that the UserAccount is a creator of.

propertyAttribute.label: next by date
propertyAttribute.comment: Next Item or Post in a given Container sorted by date.

propertyAttribute.label: parent of
propertyAttribute.comment: A child Container or Forum that this Container or Forum is a parent of.

propertyAttribute.label: has parent
propertyAttribute.comment: A Container or Forum that this Container or Forum is a child of.

propertyAttribute.label: has administrator
propertyAttribute.comment: A UserAccount that is an administrator of this Site.

propertyAttribute.label: part of
propertyAttribute.comment: A resource that the subject is a part of.

propertyAttribute.label: account of
propertyAttribute.comment: Refers to the foaf:Agent or foaf:Person who owns this sioc:UserAccount.

propertyAttribute.label: owner of
propertyAttribute.comment: A resource owned by a particular UserAccount, for example, a weblog or image gallery.

propertyAttribute.label: has discussion
propertyAttribute.comment: The discussion that is related to this Item.

propertyAttribute.label: member of
propertyAttribute.comment: A Usergroup that this UserAccount is a member of.

propertyAttribute.label: previous version
propertyAttribute.comment: Links to the previous revision of this Item or Post.

propertyAttribute.label: host of
propertyAttribute.comment: A Forum that is hosted on this Site.

propertyAttribute.label: has subscriber
propertyAttribute.comment: A UserAccount that is subscribed to this Container.

propertyAttribute.label: reply of
propertyAttribute.comment: Links to an Item or Post which this Item or Post is a reply to.

propertyAttribute.label: related to
propertyAttribute.comment: Related Posts for this Post, perhaps determined implicitly from topics or references.

propertyAttribute.label: previous by date
propertyAttribute.comment: Previous Item or Post in a given Container sorted by date.

propertyAttribute.label: has scope
propertyAttribute.comment: A resource that this Role applies to.

propertyAttribute.label: function of
propertyAttribute.comment: A UserAccount that has this Role.

propertyAttribute.label: has reply
propertyAttribute.comment: Points to an Item or Post that is a reply or response to this Item or Post.

propertyAttribute.label: has function
propertyAttribute.comment: A Role that this UserAccount has.

propertyAttribute.label: sibling
propertyAttribute.comment: An Item may have a sibling or a twin that exists in a different Container, but the siblings may differ in some small way (for example, language, category, etc.). The sibling of this Item should be self-describing (that is, it should contain all available information).

propertyAttribute.label: has space
propertyAttribute.comment: A data Space which this resource is a part of.

propertyAttribute.label: moderator of
propertyAttribute.comment: A Forum that a UserAccount is a moderator of.

propertyAttribute.label: email
propertyAttribute.comment: An electronic mail address of the UserAccount.

propertyAttribute.label: created at
propertyAttribute.comment: When this was created, in ISO 8601 format.

propertyAttribute.label: first name
propertyAttribute.comment: First (real) name of this User. Synonyms include given name or christian name.

propertyAttribute.label: ip address
propertyAttribute.comment: The IP address used when creating this Item. This can be associated with a creator. Some wiki articles list the IP addresses for the creator or modifiers when the usernames are absent.

propertyAttribute.label: last name
propertyAttribute.comment: Last (real) name of this user. Synonyms include surname or family name.

propertyAttribute.label: email sha1
propertyAttribute.comment: An electronic mail address of the UserAccount, encoded using SHA1.

propertyAttribute.label: num threads
propertyAttribute.comment: The number of Threads (AKA discussion topics) in a Forum.

propertyAttribute.label: content
propertyAttribute.comment: The content of the Item in plain text format.

propertyAttribute.label: last reply date
propertyAttribute.comment: The date and time of the last reply Post or Comment, which could be associated with a starter Item or Post or with a Thread, and expressed in ISO 8601 format.

propertyAttribute.label: num authors
propertyAttribute.comment: The number of unique authors (UserAccounts and unregistered posters) who have contributed to this Item, Thread, Post, etc.

propertyAttribute.label: num items
propertyAttribute.comment: The number of Posts (or Items) in a Forum (or a Container).

propertyAttribute.label: last item date
propertyAttribute.comment: The date and time of the last Post (or Item) in a Forum (or a Container), in ISO 8601 format.

propertyAttribute.label: name
propertyAttribute.comment: The name of a SIOC concept instance, e.g. a username for a UserAccount, group name for a Usergroup, etc.

propertyAttribute.label: id
propertyAttribute.comment: An identifier of a SIOC concept instance. For example, a user ID. Must be unique for instances of each type of SIOC concept within the same site.

propertyAttribute.label: description
propertyAttribute.comment: The content of the Post.

propertyAttribute.label: title
propertyAttribute.comment: This is the title (subject line) of the Post. Note that for a Post within a threaded discussion that has no parents, it would detail the topic thread.

propertyAttribute.label: content encoded
propertyAttribute.comment: The encoded content of the Post, contained in CDATA areas.

propertyAttribute.label: subject
propertyAttribute.comment: Keyword(s) describing subject of the Post.

propertyAttribute.label: note
propertyAttribute.comment: A note associated with this resource, for example, if it has been edited by a UserAccount.

propertyAttribute.label: last activity date
propertyAttribute.comment: The date and time of the last activity associated with a SIOC concept instance, and expressed in ISO 8601 format. This could be due to a reply Post or Comment, a modification to an Item, etc.

propertyAttribute.label: num views
propertyAttribute.comment: The number of times this Item, Thread, UserAccount profile, etc. has been viewed.

propertyAttribute.label: num replies
propertyAttribute.comment: The number of replies that this Item, Thread, Post, etc. has. Useful for when the reply structure is absent.

propertyAttribute.label: modified at
propertyAttribute.comment: When this was modified, in ISO 8601 format.

classAttribute.label: Site
classAttribute.comment: A Site can be the location of an online community or set of communities, with UserAccounts and Usergroups creating Items in a set of Containers. It can be thought of as a web-accessible data Space.

classAttribute.label: User Account
classAttribute.comment: A user account in an online community site.

classAttribute.label: Community
classAttribute.comment: Community is a high-level concept that defines an online community and what it consists of.

classAttribute.label: Role
classAttribute.comment: A Role is a function of a UserAccount within a scope of a particular Forum, Site, etc.

classAttribute.label: Thread
classAttribute.comment: A container for a series of threaded discussion Posts or Items.

classAttribute.label: Space
classAttribute.comment: A Space is a place where data resides, e.g. on a website, desktop, fileshare, etc.

classAttribute.label: User
classAttribute.comment: UserAccount is now preferred. This is a deprecated class for a User in an online community site.

classAttribute.label: Item
classAttribute.comment: An Item is something which can be in a Container.

classAttribute.label: Usergroup
classAttribute.comment: A set of UserAccounts whose owners have a common purpose or interest. Can be used for access control purposes.

classAttribute.label: Container
classAttribute.comment: An area in which content Items are contained.

classAttribute.label: Post
classAttribute.comment: An article or message that can be posted to a Forum.

classAttribute.label: Forum
classAttribute.comment: A discussion area on which Posts or entries are made.

header.author: Uldis Bojars, John G. Breslin
header.title: SIOC Core Ontology
header.description: SIOC (Semantically-Interlinked Online Communities) is an ontology for describing the information in online communities. This information can be used to export information from online communities and to link them together. The scope of the application areas that SIOC can be used for includes (and is not limited to) weblogs, message boards, mailing lists and chat channels.
